        <!-- Geolocate Tool Description -->
        <div class="wiki-description">
            <h3>Geolocate</h3>
            <p>
                The Geolocate tool is a powerful utility designed for geolocation purposes. Leveraging advanced algorithms and geospatial data, it provides users with the ability to determine the geographical location of a given point of interest. The tool is equipped with a modern and user-friendly interface, making it accessible to both novice and experienced users.
            </p>
            <strong>Features:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Image Upload:</strong> Users can upload images, and the tool extracts relevant geolocation data embedded in the image metadata.</li>
                <li><strong>Search Similar Locations:</strong> Utilizing image recognition technology, the tool can identify similar locations based on uploaded images.</li>
                <li><strong>Modern Interface:</strong> The tool features round and reactive buttons, aligning with contemporary design standards across the entire website.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Editor Tool Description -->
        <div class="wiki-description">
            <h3>Editor Tool</h3>
            <p>
                The Editor tool is a versatile notepad with a range of editing features, catering to users who need a simple yet functional platform for text and code editing. It incorporates a toolbar with various formatting options, allowing users to customize their text or code according to their preferences.
            </p>
            <strong>Key Functions:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Text Formatting:</strong> Users can toggle between bold, italic, and underline styles with the click of a button.</li>
                <li><strong>Bulleted Lists:</strong> The tool supports the creation of bulleted lists for organized content.</li>
                <li><strong>Code Blocks:</strong> Users can insert code blocks with syntax highlighting for better code readability.</li>
                <li><strong>Image Upload:</strong> The ability to seamlessly upload images directly into the editor enhances the tool's versatility.</li>
                <li><strong>Encryption Toggle:</strong> A dedicated button allows users to toggle encryption for enhanced security.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Whois Tool Description -->
        <div class="wiki-description">
            <h3>Whois Tool</h3>
            <p>
                The Whois tool is an essential utility for performing WHOIS checks on domains. This tool empowers users to retrieve detailed information about domain registrations, including ownership details, registration dates, and domain expiration information.
            </p>
            <strong>Functionality:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Domain Input:</strong> Users can input the domain they want to investigate into the provided text field.</li>
                <li><strong>Check WHOIS:</strong> The "Check" button initiates the WHOIS query, providing users with a comprehensive report.</li>
                <li><strong>Result Display:</strong> The tool displays the WHOIS information in a well-organized manner, making it easy for users to interpret.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

